      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've tried every specialist. i've tried every pill, every nerve block, every stupid therapy. nothing works. it's not about finding a \"management\" plan anymore. it's just the sheer weight of it. people act like life is some amazing gift, but when it's just constant torture, it doesn't feel like a gift. it feels like a sentence. sometimes i look at it and think, isn't it more compassionate to just let someone go when the suffering is this much? wouldn't it be more merciful to just have silence instead of this?",
